                <note rend="inline" type="source">841D.01/344a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-17T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 17, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3060. We are still awaiting the views of the British Government before reaching a
                    definite decision in regard to the proposed further note to Ireland. It is of
                    course desirable that we have these views as soon as possible if the note is to
                    be sent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
